# Fuyao Deploy and Sweep Command

Invoke as `/deploy-fuyao`.

Use toolbox wrappers under `~/.cursor/scripts`:

- single deploy helper: `deploy_fuyao.sh`
- parallel sweep orchestrator: `orchestrator.sh` (delegates to parallel engine)

## Single Deploy Path

Use when user wants one job:

```bash
bash /home/huh/.cursor/scripts/deploy_fuyao.sh \
  --helper-mode deploy \
  --task <task> \
  --branch <branch> \
  --label <label> \
  --ssh-alias Huh8.remote_kernel.fuyao \
  --remote-root /root/motion_rl \
  --project rc-wbc \
  --site fuyao_sh_n2 \
  --queue rc-wbc-4090-share \
  --experiment huh8/r01 \
  --auto-yes true
```

Use `--receipt-out <path>` and report machine-readable receipt fields (`submitted`, `job_name`, `job_id`).

## Parallel Sweep Path (Preferred for HP sweep)

Use when user wants hyperparameter combinations:

```bash
bash /home/huh/.cursor/scripts/orchestrator.sh --payload /tmp/sweep_payload.json
```

Required payload safety fields for live runs:

- `confirm_live_submit: true`
- `confirm_live_cancel: true`

Parallel policy:

- submit/validate/cancel each cycle in parallel,
- hard cap of `2` live jobs per cycle (`max_live_jobs_per_cycle`).

## Validation Policy (Anti-Fake-Job)

Do not treat submit receipt alone as success.
A combo is start-confirmed only when both pass:

1. Status probe shows running-like state (`JOB_RUNNING`/running equivalent).
2. Log probe shows training-entry markers (for example `humanoid/scripts/train.py`, `Setting seed:`).

These are written to per-combo artifacts:

- `submission_receipt.json`
- `start_validation.json`
- `cancel_validation.json`

## Task Validation (Mandatory)

- Validate task against `humanoid-gym/humanoid/envs/__init__.py` via `task_registry.register("...")`.
- Resolve ambiguity before running deploy.

## Required User-Facing Reporting

For each run, report:

- execution path (`ssh -> Huh8.remote_kernel.fuyao`),
- branch and task,
- submission status,
- job name/id (if available),
- validation status (start confirmed vs not),
- cancellation status (for sweep canary cycles),
- artifact folder path for evidence.
